You are working on a production-oriented Next.js ecommerce codebase.

Tech stack:
- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript
- Prisma
- PostgreSQL
- Tailwind CSS

Rules:
- Prefer TypeScript with explicit types for exported functions.
- Prefer server components by default unless client interactivity is required.
- Use "use client" only when necessary.
- Keep business logic out of page files when possible.
- Put reusable server logic in lib/ or services/.
- For database access, use Prisma with clear function names.
- Do not introduce unnecessary dependencies.
- Keep code modular and easy to review.
- When changing schema, also suggest migration steps.
- For API/webhook code, include error handling and logging.
- Before large edits, summarize the plan first.

<!-- Only inspect app/products, components/products, lib, and prisma. -->
Ignore node_modules, .next, dist, build, coverage.
